These mini peppermint cheesecakes will be a hit at any holiday party 🎄🎄

Mini Peppermint Cheesecakes (makes one dozen)

Crust:
▢ 1 ¼ cups crushed chocolate cookie crumbs (I used Oreos)
▢ 3 Tablespoons butter , melted
▢ 1 Tablespoon granulated sugar

Filling:

▢ ¾ cup granulated sugar
▢ 2 8-oz. packages cream cheese, softened
▢ 2 large eggs
▢ ¼ cup sour cream
▢ 3 Tablespoons heavy cream
▢ 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
▢ 1 teaspoon peppermint extract
▢ 20 Hershey’s candy cane kiss candies, chopped

Whipped Topping:

▢ 1 1/2 cups heavy cream
▢ 1/4 cup powdered sugar
▢ 2 teaspoons vanilla extract 
▢ 12 Hershey’s candy cane kiss candies

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Prepare a cupcake tin by lining with paper liners. In a small bowl, whisk together the cookie crumbs, melted butter and 1 Tablespoon sugar. Spoon 1-2 Tablespoons of the cookie mixture into each well of the cupcake tin and press down to form a crust. Bake 5 minutes in the preheated oven, then remove.
While the crust is baking, in a large bowl or the bowl of a stand mixer, beat together the sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, sour cream, 3 Tablespoons heavy cream, vanilla, peppermint extract and food coloring until smooth. Gently fold in the chopped candies. Spoon the cheesecake filling into the wells of the muffin tin, filling nearly full. Bake 20-25 minutes, or until they only jiggle slightly when you move the pan. The cheesecakes will dome while cooking and then flatten as they cool.

Refrigerate at least two hours (I prefer overnight to let them settle). For whipped topping, blend all ingredients together until stiff peaks form. Pipe onto cheesecakes and garnish with a Hershey’s kiss. 

adapted from @iheartnaptime

The easiest summer citrus sangria 🍋🍹🍊 This is always a crowd pleaser and only takes a few minutes to throw together! Recipe 👇🏻

- 2 bottles dry white wine 
- 1/2 cup citrus vodka
- 1/4 cup triple sec
- sliced citrus fruit 
- club soda 
- mint for flavor and garnish 

Stir all ingredients except club soda and mint and refrigerate for several hours. Remove and stir, then add fresh mint and top with club soda before serving.

✨ Sparkling Paloma ✨ This is THE perfect refreshing cocktail for summer! Save and share this with your friends 🍹 Recipe below:

- 1/2 grapefruit, juiced
- 2 oz. silver tequila
- 1/2-1 oz. simple syrup depending on taste 
- Prosecco 
- coarse salt to rim glass

Juice grapefruit directly into shaker. Use remaining fruit to rub around the rim of your glass so salt will stick. Add tequila and simple syrup to the shaker with grapefruit juice. Make sure you use plenty of ice to make it nice and cold. Shake, strain into glass, then top with Prosecco 🍾

Recipe below ⬇️ 

Peach Berry Slush

- 6 cups peaches (peeled and sliced)
- 2 cups strawberries (sliced)
- 2 Tablespoons honey
- 1 bottle rosé wine

Freeze fruit for at least 3 hours prior for the best consistency. Blend everything together and serve!
